<br>
DPS                Warrior &gt; Pal<br>
Tanking  Ability Warrior &gt; Pal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 3:06:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=104.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cazic NPC's to be Tauntable</span><hr size=1> Single Target Healing: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Group Healing: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Instant Healing: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Crowd Control (Root Parking): Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Interrupting Casters: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Chain Stunning: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Divine Aura Pulling: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Damage Dealing vs. Undead: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Gaining &amp; Keeping Aggro: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Ability to Solo: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
Ability to Make &quot;Non-Ideal&quot; Groups Work Well: Pal &gt; Warrior<br>
<br>
I could go on.  Paladins are better at a lot of things.  I can maybe see other pure melee classes saying they should be better or worse at offense or defense, because they have nothing else to balance any deficiencies.  We are not a pure melee class.<br>
<br>
In the past (before melee class balancing) I might have agreed that in the the high end (51+) game our drawbacks outweighed our benefits compared to warriors, or at least that you really needed to use skill and effort to make up the difference.  <br>
<br>
Post melee class balancing and post luclin, no way.  They narrowed the gap in our melee differences (e.g., narrowed/eliminated melee skill caps, increased 2hs damage &amp; added better 2hs/2hp weapons, put us on the same damage table), and gave us more useful spells (e.g., self haste, self regen, undead damage proc, group heals, efficient heal over time, stackable HP buffs).<br>
<br>
We don't need the same offensive *or* defensive abilities as warriors to be balanced with them.<br>
<br>
